<!--
  Hyderabad HITEC City – High Traffic Zone
  =========================================
  Pre-embedded OpenStreetMap network data representing the HITEC City
  Information Technology corridor in Hyderabad, Telangana, India.

  Area: ~17.440°N – 17.452°N, 78.370°E – 78.388°E
  This zone contains the highest traffic density in Hyderabad due to the
  concentration of IT campuses (Cyber Towers, DLF, Mindspace, Inorbit),
  making it an ideal testbed for multi-agent reinforcement-learning based
  traffic signal control.

  Key roads modelled:
    • Madhapur Main Road (E–W, primary, 4 lanes)
    • HITEC City Main Road / Hitech City Road (E–W, primary, 4 lanes)
    • Ayyappa Society Road connector (N–S, secondary)
    • Cyber Towers Road (N–S, primary, 4 lanes)
    • DLF Cyber City Road (N–S, secondary)
    • Mindspace Road (N–S, secondary)
    • South Madhapur Road (E–W, secondary)
    • Diagonal connector: Madhapur–Mindspace shortcut

  Traffic signals at all major intersections (12 controlled junctions).

  Source: Based on OpenStreetMap (© OpenStreetMap contributors, ODbL)
  Generated for: IUTMS – Intelligent Urban Traffic Management System
-->
